        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 1:15PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>Showers and thunderstorms with gusty winds will continue to develop
over northern Berkeley County this afternoon. These storms may drift
close enough to the eastern portions of Lake Marion to produce
locally gusty winds and cloud to water lightning. Boaters should
consider seeking safe harbor. Remember, lightning can strike many
miles away from a thunderstorm.
</description>
        <instruction>Boaters on the eastern portions of Lake Marion should consider
seeking safe harbor. If caught on the open water, stay as low as
possible and wear a personal flotation device. Remember, if you can
hear thunder you are at risk for being struck by lightning.</instruction>
